The paper deals with the security of Industrial Control Systems (ICS) and proposes a novel security metric based on AND/OR graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with cyber-physical dependencies among network components, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also leverages state-of-the-art techniques from the field of logical satisfiability optimization, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses a case study where the proposed system is used to analyze the security posture of a realistic water transport network, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a tool called META4ICS, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
